# Sprint 50c-2/3 — bundle the Dylan-side lexer + the macro engine
# smoke into one module (`dylan-lexer`). Lets the smoke call the real
# lexer's `<token>` machinery, group-balance hash-prefixed groups,
# and use `token-source-text` to round-trip every keyword.
#
# `nod-driver build --project dylan-macro-smoke.prj` produces
# `dylan-macro-smoke.exe` alongside this file.
#
# Sprint 50d unblocked the duplicate-main collision by adding
# `start_function` to the .prj schema (smoke uses `smoke-main` so the
# parser's `main` doesn't collide). Adding `dylan-parser.dylan` to
# `sources` still surfaces a runtime "format-out: format string is not
# a <byte-string> (raw 0x0)" before `smoke-main` runs — likely a
# global-registration ordering bug specific to the 3-file bundle. The
# entry-name plumbing is correct (2-file `smoke-main` runs perfectly);
# the new blocker is a separate AOT init-order issue. See SPRINTS.md
# "Sprint 50c-4 — registration-order blocker in 3-file bundle".

name           = "dylan-macro-smoke"
sources        = ["dylan-lexer.dylan", "dylan-macro-smoke.dylan"]
output         = "dylan-macro-smoke.exe"
start_function = "smoke-main"
